A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Motor Vehicles – Plug–In Electric Drive Vehicles in HOV Lane – Termination
3 Date
4 FOR the purpose of extending the termination date of a provision of law that authorizes
5 certain plug–in electric drive vehicles to use high occupancy vehicle (HOV) lanes
6 regardless of the number of passengers in the vehicles; and generally relating to the
7 use of HOV lanes by plug–in electric drive vehicles.
8 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
9 Article – Transportation
10 Section 25–108
11 Annotated Code of Maryland
12 (2020 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
13 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
14 Chapter 121 of the Acts of the General Assembly of 2023
15 Section 2
16 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
17 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
18 Article – Transportation
19 25–108.
20 (a) In this section, “HOV lane” means a high occupancy vehicle lane designated
21 by the State Highway Administration whose use is restricted by a traffic control device
22 during specified times to vehicles carrying at least a specified number of occupants.
23 (b) This section applies only to a plug–in electric drive vehicle that has a
24 maximum speed capability of at least 65 miles per hour.
