1 (c) A plug–in electric drive vehicle for which a permit has been applied for and
2 obtained from the Administration under this section may use an HOV lane at all times
3 regardless of the number of passengers in the vehicle.
4 (d) (1) The Administration, the State Highway Administration, and the
5 Department of State Police may consult to design a permit to designate a vehicle as a
6 plug–in electric drive vehicle authorized to use an HOV lane.
7 (2) The Administration shall charge a fee, not to exceed $20, for issuing a
8 permit under this section.
9 (3) The Administration, on the recommendation of the State Highway
10 Administration, may limit the number of permits issued to ensure HOV lane operations are
11 not degraded to an unacceptable level.
12 (e) On or before January 1 each year, the Administration and the State Highway
13 Administration jointly shall report to the Governor and, in accordance with § 2–1257 of the
14 State Government Article, the General Assembly on the effect of the use of the plug–in
15 electric drive vehicle permits issued under this section on the operation of HOV lanes in
16 the State.
